# Offer of Internship — AI Intern

Date: [OFFER_DATE]

To: [CANDIDATE_NAME]  
Address: [CANDIDATE_ADDRESS]  
Email: [CANDIDATE_EMAIL]

Dear [CANDIDATE_NAME],

We are pleased to offer you an internship with Omninuera in the position of AI Intern. This letter sets out the principal terms of the internship. Please read carefully, sign where indicated, and return a scanned copy to [HR_EMAIL].

1. Position and Reporting
- Position Title: AI Intern.  
- Reporting Line: You will report to [IMMEDIATE_MANAGER_NAME], [IMMEDIATE_MANAGER_TITLE], or such other person as Omninuera may designate. Day-to-day supervision and assignments will be provided by your reporting manager.

2. Company
- Company: Omninuera.

3. Duration and Start Date
- Duration: 3 months.  
- Start Date: To be mutually agreed. (Placeholder: [START_DATE]). The internship is temporary and will end on the date three months after the agreed start date unless extended by mutual written agreement.

4. Work Location and Jurisdiction Reference
- Work Location: Completely remote.  
- Jurisdiction Reference: The candidate is based in Bengaluru for jurisdiction and administrative purposes.

5. Employment Type and Expected Hours
- Employment Type: Internship (temporary, training-oriented).  
- Expected Weekly Hours: Approximately 20–40 hours per week, with flexibility depending on project needs and mutual agreement. Specific weekly schedule will be set by your manager.

6. Compensation
- Stipend: INR 10,000 per month (paid monthly). This stipend is a training allowance and not a salary. Applicable taxes or statutory withholdings, if any, will be handled according to company policy and applicable law.

7. Probation and Termination
- Internship Probation: The first [PROBATION_PERIOD_DAYS] days/weeks of the internship may be treated as an initial evaluation period during which performance, fit, and alignment with the role will be assessed. (Placeholder: [PROBATION_PERIOD_DAYS]; typical practice is 14–30 days).  
- Termination: Either party may terminate the internship at any time. Omninuera may terminate the internship with immediate effect for cause (including but not limited to breach of company policies, misconduct, or unsatisfactory performance). For non-cause terminations, the company or the intern will provide reasonable written notice (typical practice: 7 days) or payment in lieu of notice where applicable. This internship does not create any expectation of continued employment beyond the stated duration.

8. Confidentiality
- During the internship and at all times thereafter, you must keep confidential all proprietary, business-sensitive, technical and other non-public information of Omninuera and its clients, and not disclose such information except as required in the course of performing your internship duties or as required by law. You will be required to sign the Company’s standard confidentiality/non-disclosure agreement.

9. Intellectual Property (IP) Assignment
- All work product, inventions, discoveries, developments, processes, algorithms, code, documentation, designs, and other works (collectively, "Work Product") conceived, developed, or created by you, alone or jointly, during the internship and related to Omninuera’s business, research, or actual or demonstrably anticipated projects shall be the exclusive property of Omninuera. You agree to disclose promptly such Work Product and to assign and transfer all right, title and interest in and to such Work Product to Omninuera and to execute all documents and take such acts as may be reasonably requested to effectuate such assignment. You acknowledge that this IP assignment is standard for interns engaged in company projects.

10. Compliance with Company Policies
- You must comply with Omninuera’s policies and procedures, including but not limited to acceptable use, data protection, security, and workplace conduct policies. The company reserves the right to update policies from time to time; continued participation in the internship constitutes acceptance of those policies.

11. Background Checks and Pre-Employment Requirements
- This offer is conditional on satisfactory completion of any pre-employment/engagement checks that Omninuera may require, which may include identity verification, educational verification, and criminal background checks where applicable. You will be notified if any checks are required and what information is needed.

12. Statutory Benefits and Disclaimers (India)
- This internship is a temporary training arrangement. Statutory benefits typically available to employees (such as Provident Fund, Gratuity, or paid leave) may not be applicable to interns; applicability will be governed by the nature of the arrangement and applicable Indian law. This letter does not constitute legal advice. Omninuera will comply with applicable Indian laws and regulations pertaining to internships and any statutory obligations as required.

13. Data Protection and Privacy
- By accepting this offer, you consent to Omninuera processing your personal data for recruitment, on-boarding, and engagement-related purposes in accordance with the company’s privacy policy.

14. Other Terms
- External Work/Conflicts of Interest: During the internship you should avoid activities that conflict with your obligations and responsibilities to Omninuera. Prior disclosure and approval must be obtained for any outside work that may create a conflict of interest.
- Equipment and Expenses: The internship is remote. Any company-provided equipment or expense reimbursement will be provided as expressly agreed in writing.

15. Acceptance
Please sign and date below to indicate your acceptance of this offer and the terms set out herein, and return a scanned copy to [HR_EMAIL] by [OFFER_EXPIRY_DATE] (placeholder: [OFFER_EXPIRY_DATE]).

We look forward to having you join Omninuera.

Sincerely,

For Omninuera

